tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE SwimmingEventRankings (
    event_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    event_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    swimmer_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    swim_time TIME NOT NULL,
    ranking INT
);

CREATE TABLE EventRankings (
    event_id INT NOT NULL,
    event_name VARCHAR(255),
    ranking INT,
    athlete_name VARCHAR(255),
    country VARCHAR(50),
    PRIMARY KEY (event_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Standings (
    standing_id INT NOT NULL,
    event_id INT,
    athlete_name VARCHAR(255),
    country VARCHAR(50),
    total_points INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (standing_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (event_id) REFERENCES EventRankings(event_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Updates (
    update_id INT NOT NULL,
    event_id INT,
    update_text TEXT,
    update_time TIMESTAMP,
    PRIMARY KEY (update_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (event_id) REFERENCES EventRankings(event_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Ranking (
  Ranking_ID INT PRIMARY KEY,
  Event_ID INT,
  Participant_ID INT,
  Event_Rank INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (Event_ID) REFERENCES Event(Event_ID),
  FOREIGN KEY (Participant_ID) REFERENCES Participant(Participant_ID)
);

CREATE TABLE Standings (
  Standings_ID INT PRIMARY KEY,
  Event_ID INT,
  Participant_ID INT,
  Standings_Position INT,
  Standings_Time TIME,
  FOREIGN KEY (Event_ID) REFERENCES Event(Event_ID),
  FOREIGN KEY (Participant_ID) REFERENCES Participant(Participant_ID)
);

CREATE TABLE competition (
    competition_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    event_id INT NOT NULL,
    team_id INT NOT NULL,
    swimmer_id INT NOT NULL,
    time FLOAT NOT NULL,
    rank INT NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (event_id) REFERENCES event(event_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (swimmer_id) REFERENCES swimmer(swimmer_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES team(team_id)
);

CREATE TABLE standing (
    standing_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    competition_id INT NOT NULL,
    rank INT NOT NULL,
    points INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (competition_id) REFERENCES competition(competition_id)
);
